About[edit | edit source]

This page feeds the Customs Interactive Map.

How to edit this table[edit | edit source]

There are two options: "Edit" and "Edit Source". To be honest... If you do not feel comfortable editing the SOURCE version of this page, you should not be attempting to edit the dynamic map at all. Instead, consider telling us on the Wiki Discord about any changes that need to be made. Without further ado:

New Entries[edit | edit source]

  1. Open up the map on a separate window, and CTRL + Left Click. This will give you the coordinates you need to place in the table below for the information you are adding
  2. Go to Edit Source on this page
  3. Scroll to the bottom, and copy/paste the '|-' and an existing entry to a new line, like this:

  1. Update the newly pasted line with the information you are putting in. Note that for the proper icon to appear (reference the Legend on the left side of the map), you need to use a matching Category/Name from the Legend. (ie; 'Scav Spawn', 'Stash', etc)
  2. Save changes.

Updating Existing Entries[edit | edit source]

The steps are the same as adding a new entry, meaning you update the source of this page. To find the correct table item to update though, you can reference the 'hidden' coordinate data of the thing you are editing. Click the icon that you are editing, then highlight all the text in the pop-up.
